{
    "title": "When to Be Formal",
    "level": "C1",
    "pattern": {
        "title": "Teitittely: Voisitteko...?",
        "summary": "Finland is casual, but the formal you (te + plural verb) still earns respect with elderly people, in customer service, and in official calls: Voisitteko auttaa? = Could you (formally) help? Knowing when to switch - and how to ask permission to switch back (sopiiks, et mä sinuttelen?) - is real C1 skill.",
        "examples": [
            "Anteeksi, voisitteko auttaa hetken? = Excuse me, could you help for a moment?",
            "Käykö teille torstai? = Does Thursday work for you?",
            "Sopiiks, et mä sinuttelen? = Is it ok if I use the informal you?"
        ]
    },
